15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0"><div class="component-rendition" data-aspect-ratio="3:2" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.0"><div class="component-image loaded" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.0.0"><span data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.0.0.0"><img alt="Summer Cocktails" src="http://media.gq.com/photos/559b00cc2ca27595129895f6/3:2/w_806/Screen Shot 2015-07-06 at 6.05.34 PM.png"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=&amp;t=" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=&amp;t=" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F559b00cc2ca27595129895f6%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2FScreen%20Shot%202015-07-06%20at%206.05.34%20PM.png&amp;description=" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-pinterest"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F559b00cc2ca27595129895f6%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2FScreen%20Shot%202015-07-06%20at%206.05.34%20PM.png&amp;description=" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-pinterest.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-pinterest.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.2.0.1.0:$share-item-pinterest.0.1">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure><h2 class="dek" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.3">Our twists on the classics will help you get your drank on in style</h2><div class="body-text" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4"><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.0">Meet our trusty barkeep, Nicholas Bennett , from Manhattan&apos;s Porchlight bar. You can trust everything he says because that stache doesn&apos;t lie. He&apos;s here to show you how to make five cocktails that are perfect for summer and impressing everyone you know. There&apos;s no reason you should be drinking a boring vodka tonic, when you can make &quot;The 28th &amp; Tonic.&quot; We realize these take a little extra grunt work, (the &quot;whip shake&quot; is intense) but we know you can handle it. Make the mustache proud. </p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1"><strong>Merry Melodies Martini</strong></p><div class="embed figure" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.2"><figure class="embedded-video"><iframe src="http://player.cnevids.com/embed/559ae15961646d22dd0a0000/51097beb8ef9aff9f5000005" height="" width=""></iframe></figure></div><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.3">If you can get past ordering something with &quot;teeny&quot; in the title, you&apos;ll realize that apple martinis are damn delicious. This one, with its nifty twist (unaged apple brandy), is all kinds of yummy for the dudeliest of dudes. Own the frivolity and make this &quot;Merry Melodies&quot; martini with some confidence. Happy prancing!</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.5"><em>What&apos;s Shakin&apos;:</em></p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.6">.75 oz Dolin blanc vermouth</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.7">.75 oz unaged apple brandy</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.8">1.25 oz Ford&apos;s gin</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.9"><em>Garnish &amp; Glass:</em> Blackberry &amp; Collins</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.a"><strong>Rhubarb Rhubarb</strong></p><div class="embed figure" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.b"><figure class="embedded-video"><iframe src="http://player.cnevids.com/embed/5595902f61646d3a48130000/51097beb8ef9aff9f5000005" height="" width=""></iframe></figure></div><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.c">Rhubarb Rhubarb &#x2013; the drink so nice they named it twice&#x2026; either that, or they were wayyy hungover on cocktail christening day. The newly fashionable fruit makes a mean simple syrup and amaro (to the uninitiated - that&apos;s an Italian digestif). The coolest ingredient is still the egg white, though. Nothing says boss like froth.</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.d"><em>What&apos;s Shakin&apos;:</em></p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.e">.75 oz lemon juice</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.f">.75 oz rhubarb simple syrup</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.g">.5 oz Zucca (rhubarb-based amaro)</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.h">1.5 oz Ford&apos;s gin</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.i">An egg white</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.j"><em>Garnish &amp; Glass:</em> The Froth (is garnish enough) &amp; Coupe</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.k"><strong>Gun Metal Blue</strong></p><div class="embed figure" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.l"><figure class="embedded-video"><iframe src="http://player.cnevids.com/embed/55958e5c61646d5ac6070000/51097beb8ef9aff9f5000005" height="" width=""></iframe></figure></div><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.m">&quot;Bright, blue, colorful &#x2013; what&apos;s not to love about it?&quot; Nich asks. All of those words <em>kinda</em> mean the same thing, so we&apos;ll suggest you might also love the rich combination of orange and smoky flavor that results from &quot;flaming the oils&quot; out of an orange twist. The cocktail is delicious and you get to set something on fire &#x2013; <em>now</em> what&apos;s not to love?</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.n"><em>What&apos;s Shakin&apos;:</em></p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.o">.75 oz lime juice</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.p">.25 oz bitter cinnamon simple syrup</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.q">.25 oz peach brandy</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.r">.5 oz &quot;bright, blue, colorful&quot; Cura&#xE7;ao</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.s">1.5 oz Mezcal Vida</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.t"><em>Garnish &amp; Glass:</em> Flamed Orange Coin &amp; Coupe</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.u"><strong>The 28th &amp; Tonic</strong></p><div class="embed figure" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.v"><figure class="embedded-video"><iframe src="http://player.cnevids.com/embed/55958ca161646d3a512c0000/51097beb8ef9aff9f5000005" height="" width=""></iframe></figure></div><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.w">Nicholas isn&apos;t necessary saying only Neanderthals and minors with their brother&apos;s ID order standard v&amp;ts, but he admits this recipe is more &quot;high class. &quot; Nothing says mature sophistication like <em>elder</em>berry syrup and sparkling wine. Anyone stepping up to ask for, &quot;The 28th &amp; Tonic, my good sir!&quot; is onto some classy shit.</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.x"><em>What&apos;s Shakin&apos;:</em></p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.y">.5 oz fresh lemon juice</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.z">.5 oz Tomr&apos;s tonic syrup</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.10">.5 oz Elderberry syrup</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.11">1.5 oz Tito&apos;s vodka</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.12">Top with sparkling wine</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.13"><em>Garnish &amp; Glass:</em> Lemon Wheel &amp; Wine Glass</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.14"><strong>Behind the Mule</strong></p><div class="embed figure" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.15"><figure class="embedded-video"><iframe src="http://player.cnevids.com/embed/55958a7461646d3a51240000/51097beb8ef9aff9f5000005" height="" width=""></iframe></figure></div><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.16">Sweet or savory? My friends, thanks to chicken n waffles and this cocktail, we no longer have to choose! The vinegar creates a &quot;nice savory note,&quot; says Nich, while the berry flavor will help you keep on channeling those sweet ~summer vibes. ~</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.17"><em>What&apos;s Shakin&apos;:</em></p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.18">1.5 oz Dickel White whisky</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.19">.5 oz Katz&apos;s Rock &amp; Rye</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1a">.5 oz fresh lime juice</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1b">.5 oz ginger simple syrup</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1c">.25 oz raspberry vinegar</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1d">Top with soda</p><p data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.4.1e"><em>Garnish &amp; Glass:</em> Raspberries &amp; Collins</p></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=summer&#32;cocktails" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">summer cocktails</a></li><li data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=summer" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">summer </a></li><li data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="../search?tags=drinking" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">drinking</a></li><li data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3"><a href="../search?tags=cocktails" data-reactid=".15b0f1sw1kw.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3.0">cocktails</a></li><li data-